        <page n="01" image="pa.fr.vs.1864.03.09.01">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Speech of J. M'D. Sharpe, Esq.</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"The first and highest duty of a State is protection to her citizens in
                    life, liberty and property. Protection is the price of allegiance, and
                    allegiance is the duty that follows protection. Where one of these duties dies,
                    the other dies with it.--They are reciprocal, co-extensive and co-ordinate
                    obligations."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Prints transcript of a speech supporting compensation for military damages
                    in border counties given in the Pennsylvania House of Representatives by J. M'D
                    Sharpe.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
